SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1018.1 of Title 56, unless there
14
15
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall submit a request to
16
17
the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for an exemption from
17
18
the provisions of 42 C.F.R., Section 441.301(c)(1)(vi) to allow
18
19
providers of Medicaid home- and community-based services in rural
19
20
counties of this state to provide case management and develop the
20
21
required person-centered plan. As used in this subsection, “rural
21
22
counties” means counties with a population of not more than sixty
22
23
thousand (60,000), according to the most recent Federal Decennial
23
24
Census.
